{{! /freestyle/insights — patterns observed in the documented sequence archive }}

<div class="hero hero-sm">
  <div>
    {{#if navigation.breadcrumbs}}
    <nav class="breadcrumb" aria-label="Breadcrumb">
      {{#each navigation.breadcrumbs}}
        {{#if href}}<a href="{{href}}">{{label}}</a> <span class="breadcrumb-sep">/</span> {{else}}<span>{{label}}</span>{{/if}}
      {{/each}}
    </nav>
    {{/if}}
    <h1>{{page.title}}</h1>
    {{#if page.intro}}<p class="hero-subtitle">{{page.intro}}</p>{{/if}}
  </div>
</div>

<div class="wrapper">

  <p>
    These tables describe patterns within a documented archive of competitive freestyle
    sequences: which tricks recur, which ones link others together, and which players
    showed the widest range. They describe the archive on hand, not the sport as a whole.
    Unfamiliar terms are explained in the
    <a href="/freestyle/glossary">freestyle glossary</a>.
  </p>

  {{! ═══ Vocabulary ═════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ }}
  <section class="content-section">
    <div class="section-heading">
      <h2>Vocabulary</h2>
    </div>
    <p class="section-intro">Which tricks and modifiers appear most across the documented record.</p>

    <h3 class="content-subheading">Most Used Tricks</h3>
    <div class="records-table-wrap">
      <table class="records-table records-table-sm">
        <thead>
          <tr>
            <th class="col-rank">#</th>
            <th>Trick</th>
            <th class="col-adds">ADD</th>
            <th>Frequency</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          {{#each content.mostUsed}}
          <tr>
            <td class="col-rank">{{rank}}</td>
            <td>{{name}}</td>
            <td class="col-adds">{{adds}}</td>
            <td>{{label}}</td>
          </tr>
          {{/each}}
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>

    <h3 class="content-subheading">Most Used Modifiers</h3>
    <p class="section-intro">How many canonical tricks carry each modifier. This is dictionary usage, not competitive frequency.</p>
    <div class="records-table-wrap">
      <table class="records-table records-table-sm">
        <thead>
          <tr>
            <th class="col-rank">#</th>
            <th>Modifier</th>
            <th>Type</th>
            <th class="col-num">Tricks</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          {{#each content.mostUsedModifiers}}
          <tr>
            <td class="col-rank">{{rank}}</td>
            <td>{{name}}</td>
            <td class="detail-muted">{{type}}</td>
            <td class="col-num">{{count}}</td>
          </tr>
          {{/each}}
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>

    <h3 class="content-subheading">Most Influential Connectors</h3>
    <p class="section-intro">Tricks appearing most often as transition points between other tricks in a sequence.</p>
    <div class="records-table-wrap">
      <table class="records-table records-table-sm">
        <thead>
          <tr>
            <th class="col-rank">#</th>
            <th>Trick</th>
            <th class="col-adds">ADD</th>
            <th>Connections</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          {{#each content.connectors}}
          <tr>
            <td class="col-rank">{{rank}}</td>
            <td>{{name}}</td>
            <td class="col-adds">{{adds}}</td>
            <td>{{label}}</td>
          </tr>
          {{/each}}
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>
  </section>

  {{! ═══ Sequence Structure ═════════════════════════════════════════════════ }}
  <section class="content-section">
    <div class="section-heading">
      <h2>Sequence Structure</h2>
    </div>
    <p class="section-intro">How tricks connect into chains across the documented sequences.</p>

    <h3 class="content-subheading">Most Common Trick Transitions</h3>
    <div class="records-table-wrap">
      <table class="records-table records-table-sm">
        <thead>
          <tr>
            <th class="col-rank">#</th>
            <th>From</th>
            <th>To</th>
            <th class="col-num">Count</th>
            <th class="col-num">Players</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          {{#each content.transitions}}
          <tr>
            <td class="col-rank">{{rank}}</td>
            <td>{{from}}</td>
            <td>{{to}}</td>
            <td class="col-num">{{count}}</td>
            <td class="col-num">{{players}}</td>
          </tr>
          {{/each}}
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>

    <h3 class="content-subheading">Notable Documented Sequences</h3>
    <p class="section-intro">High total-ADD sequences preserved in the archive. ADD is the sum of all tricks in the chain. These are examples drawn from the documented record, not a ranking of the hardest sequences ever performed.</p>
    <div class="records-table-wrap">
      <table class="records-table records-table-sm">
        <thead>
          <tr>
            <th class="col-rank">#</th>
            <th>Player</th>
            <th class="col-adds">Year</th>
            <th class="col-adds">ADD</th>
            <th class="col-adds">Length</th>
            <th>Sequence</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          {{#each content.notableSequences}}
          <tr>
            <td class="col-rank">{{rank}}</td>
            <td>{{player}}</td>
            <td class="col-adds">{{year}}</td>
            <td class="col-adds">{{adds}}</td>
            <td class="col-adds">{{length}}</td>
            <td class="col-message">{{sequence}}</td>
          </tr>
          {{/each}}
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>
  </section>

  {{! ═══ Player Diversity ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════ }}
  <section class="content-section">
    <div class="section-heading">
      <h2>Player Diversity</h2>
    </div>
    <p class="section-intro">Players using the widest variety of distinct tricks across the documented sequences.</p>
    <div class="records-table-wrap">
      <table class="records-table records-table-sm">
        <thead>
          <tr>
            <th class="col-rank">#</th>
            <th>Player</th>
            <th class="col-num">Unique Tricks</th>
            <th>Years Active</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          {{#each content.diversePlayers}}
          <tr>
            <td class="col-rank">{{rank}}</td>
            <td>{{player}}</td>
            <td class="col-num">{{uniqueTricks}}</td>
            <td>{{yearsActive}}</td>
          </tr>
          {{/each}}
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>
  </section>

  {{! ═══ Archive Notes ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════ }}
  <section class="content-section">
    <div class="section-heading">
      <h2>Archive Notes</h2>
    </div>
    <p class="section-intro">What this data is, and what it is not.</p>
    <p>
      The sequence tables draw on a documented archive of 395 Sick3 format sequences spanning
      roughly 2001 to 2025, where each trick carries a mechanically verifiable ADD value. Sick3
      submissions are one slice of competitive freestyle, not a complete record, so these are
      patterns within the archive rather than conclusions about the sport overall.
    </p>
    <p>
      Frequencies count how often a trick appears in those sequences. Modifier tricks such as
      pixie, ducking, and spinning have no fixed standalone ADD; they are counted by mention only.
      Some sequence attributions were recovered from surrounding context rather than a direct
      record, so individual rows carry varying confidence. The modifier-usage table above is a
      separate, live count from the trick dictionary and updates with the dictionary itself.
    </p>
  </section>

</div>
